ers.\nHere, we report that experimental and molecular dynamics findings using various\nmutants support this view of the swing mechanism. The finding that mutants of\namino acids in AQP2 corresponding to the stick of the swing mechanism cause\nsevere recessive nephrogenic diabetes insipidus (NDI) demonstrates the critical\nrole of the swing mechanism for the aquaporin function. We report first that\nthe inter-subunit hydrophobic interaction in aquaporin 0 drives the\nelectrostatic opening of the aquaporin pore at the atomic level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Apr 2013 09:56:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-04-23"}
